Security 101 Homework: Security Reporting
Part I: Symantec
For Part 1 of your homework assignment, you should primarily use the Symantec Internet Security Threat Report along with independent research to answer the following questions.

What is formjacking?
JavaScript code that is injected into websites to steal credit card information. That information is then sold on the underground markets.

How many websites are compromised each month with formjacking code? 
4,818 different websites were hit by formjacking code.

What is Powershell?
PowerShell is a command-line shell. It is used for automating tasks within Windows. The shell is built on .NET framework and can also be used for configuration management.

What was the annual percentage increase in malicious Powershell scripts?
1000% in 2018 that were blocked

What is a coinminer?
Coinminers is type of program used to mine cryptocurrency. One example being Bitcoin.

How much can data from a single credit card can be sold for? 
$45 for a single card and up to $2.2 million each month depending on number of cards that are stolen.

How did Magecart successfully attack Ticketmaster?  Magecart loaded malicious code into web browsers by compromising a 3rd party chat bot 

What is one reason why there has been a growth of formjacking? 
The reason seems to be that cryptocurrency has been losing value. Using formjacking to see consumer information is a more reliable income.

Cryptojacking dropped by what percentage between January and December 2018?
It had dropped by 52%. However there were still 3.5 million cryptojacking events in dec. 2018

If a web page contains a coinmining script, what happens? 
While visiting said site it will use your system resources to “mine” cryptocurrency as long as you are on the site.

How does an exploit kit work? 
Exploit kit is a tool used to search for vulnerabilities within a system. Once one is found it can be used to download and run malware.

What does the criminal group SamSam specialize in? 
Ransomware

How many SamSam attacks did Symantec find evidence of in 2018? 
67 attacks mostly against U.S. organizations.

Even though ransomware attacks declined in 2017-2018, what was one dramatic change that occurred? 
Originally consumers were being hit the hardest by ransomware. In 2017 it started to lean towards businesses with it increasing to 81% in 2018

In 2018, what was the primary ransomware distribution method? 
Email, it is still the largest form of communication used in most companies.

What operating systems do most types of ransomware attacks still target?
Windows-based computers.

What are “living off the land” attacks? What is the advantage to hackers? 
Is the use of off-the-shelf tools. Example being PowerShell scripts. The main advantage is it can help attackers hide by using legitimate processes.
What is an example of a tool that’s used in “living off the land” attacks?
PowerShell scripts and/or macros within Office files.

What are zero-day exploits?
As discussed in the previous week. It is an attack that occurs the day a weakness is discovered before the victim is aware of it.

By what percentage did zero-day exploits decline in 2018? 
A decrease of 4%. 23% known in 2018. 27% in 2017

What are two techniques that worms such as Emotet and Qakbot use?
Password dumbing from memory and brute-forcing access to networks

What are supply chain attacks? By how much did they increase in 2018?
An attack that exploits 3rd party services and software. It can hijack  software updates or inject malicious code into legitimate software. 78% increase in 2018

What challenge do supply chain attacks and living off the land attacks highlight for organizations? 
Attacks are increasing by using trusted channels, using fileless attacks. Or the use of legitimate tools such as PowerShell

The 20 most active groups tracked by Symantec targeted an average of how many organizations between 2016 and 2018? 
55 organizations in the past 3 years.

How many individuals or organizations were indicted for cyber criminal activities in 2018? What are some of the countries that these entities were from? 
49 individuals or organizations. Countries were Russia, China, Iran and North Korea.

When it comes to the increased number of cloud cybersecurity attacks, what is the common theme? 
Poor configuration.

What is the implication for successful cloud exploitation that provides access to memory locations that are normally forbidden? 
A single physical system exploited could leak data from several cloud instances

What are two examples of the above cloud attack? 
Speculative Store Bypass and Foreshadow

Regarding Internet of Things (IoT) attacks, what were the two most common infected devices and what percentage of IoT attacks were attributed to them? 
Routers and connected cameras. 75% and 15% with routers being the most targeted

What is the Mirai worm and what does it do? 
A Distributed denial of service worm

Why was Mirai the third most common IoT threat in 2018? 
Mirai is always evolving and adding new exploits. Devices also remaining unpatched.

What was unique about VPNFilter with regards to IoT threats?
It was able to survive a reboot.

What type of attack targeted the Democratic National Committee in 2019? 
Spear-phishing attack. An email appearing to be from the U.S. Department of state.

What were 48% of  malicious email attachments in 2018? 
            48% were office files. Up from 5% in 2017

What were the top two malicious email themes in 2018? 
Bill and Email delivery failure emails

What was the top malicious email attachment type in 2018? 
.doc, .dot

Which country had the highest email phishing rate? Which country had the lowest email phishing rate?
Highest: Saudi Arabia - 1 in 675
Lowest: Canada - 1 in 4,308


What is Emotet and how much did it jump in 2018? 
Emotet is a financial Trojan. Up 12% from 2017 (16% in 2018 and 4% in 2017)

What was the top malware threat of the year? How many of those attacks were blocked?
Heur.AdvML.C, 43,999,373 attacks blocked (52.1%)

Malware primarily attacks which type of operating system? 
Windows

What was the top coinminer of 2018 and how many of those attacks were blocked? 
JS.Webcoinminer, 2,768,721 attacks blocked (49.7%)


What were the top three financial Trojans of 2018? 
Ramnit, Zbot, and Emotet

What was the most common avenue of attack in 2018? 
Spear-phishing. Used by 65% of known groups

What is destructive malware? By what percent did these attacks increase in 2018? 
Is a type of malware commonly used to destroy a system. This can be done by deleting or wiping files that are required for the operating system.

What was the top user name used in IoT attacks? 
Root (38.1%)

What was the top password used in IoT attacks? 
123456 (24.6%)

What were the top three protocols used in IoT attacks? What were the top two ports used in IoT attacks? 
Top 3 protocols: telnet (90.9%), http (6.6%), https (1.05)
Top 2 ports: 23 Telent (85.0%), 80 World Wide Web HTTP (6.5%)

In the underground economy, how much can someone get for the following? 

Stolen or fake identity: $0.10-1.50
Stolen medical records: $0.10-35
Hacker for hire: $100+
Single credit card with full details: $0.50-20
500 social media followers: $2-6
